WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:01.235
.

00:01.335 --> 00:02.170
- So you bust a sex party
and find a nun.

00:04.038 --> 00:07.608
- You saw who was there.
Politicians, police.

00:07.608 --> 00:09.677
- The johns, they must know
who threw the party.

00:09.677 --> 00:10.978
- They're not saying.

00:10.978 --> 00:13.013
Somebody knows how these girls
got caught up.

00:13.013 --> 00:16.584
- Is there someone at the school
we should be looking at?

00:16.584 --> 00:18.419
- What's the monsignor
doing here?

00:18.419 --> 00:20.554
- He has made some very serious
allegations against Tucker.

00:20.554 --> 00:22.556
- Sex trafficking,
corruption--

00:22.556 --> 00:24.258
- They really set me up good.
[cell phone buzzes]

00:24.258 --> 00:26.894
- 1PP wants to see me.

00:26.894 --> 00:28.496
- Lieutenant, what's going on?

00:28.496 --> 00:31.265
- I'm out,
effective immediately.

00:39.073 --> 00:41.041
male narrator:
In the criminal justice system,

00:41.041 --> 00:42.343
sexually based offenses

00:42.343 --> 00:44.745
are considered
especially heinous.

00:44.745 --> 00:47.014
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:47.014 --> 00:48.782
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:48.782 --> 00:50.351
are members of an elite squad

00:50.351 --> 00:52.520
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:52.520 --> 00:54.388
These are their stories.

00:55.923 --> 00:58.058
- I know having your lieutenant
transferred abruptly

00:58.058 --> 01:01.829
is unsettling,
but ours is not to reason why.

01:01.829 --> 01:04.365
- How long is Liv gonna be gone?

01:04.365 --> 01:05.833
- Best hope--temporarily.

01:05.833 --> 01:07.801
For now, keep doing your jobs.

01:07.801 --> 01:10.438
You're in good hands
with the sergeant here.

01:11.805 --> 01:15.209
- First off, I was as blindsided
by this as all of you,

01:15.209 --> 01:16.644
and second,

01:16.644 --> 01:19.980
I'm gonna need your help.

01:19.980 --> 01:22.483
- Copy that, Sergeant.
- What are we supposed to do?

01:22.483 --> 01:24.352
- Leads me to my third point.

01:24.352 --> 01:25.953
The lieutenant was recused

01:25.953 --> 01:27.721
because of the allegations
against Captain Tucker.

01:27.721 --> 01:29.490
- So what's that got
to do with Liv?

01:29.490 --> 01:32.660
- I can't speak to that,
and neither should any of you,

01:32.660 --> 01:34.228
but this is still our case,

01:34.228 --> 01:36.630
and since charges have been
made against Tucker,

01:36.630 --> 01:39.233
Barba's been pressuring us
to follow up on them,

01:39.233 --> 01:41.502
so start following up.

01:46.240 --> 01:48.376
- If Detectives
Russo and Jefferson

01:48.376 --> 01:51.645
claim they told me
about this ring, they're lying.

01:51.645 --> 01:54.515
I called them in
on a completely separate matter.

01:54.515 --> 01:55.916
- They're alleging
you blackmailed them

01:55.916 --> 01:57.518
into cutting you
in on the operation.

01:57.518 --> 01:58.819
- They're dirty.

01:58.819 --> 02:01.389
SVU busted them in the raid.

02:01.389 --> 02:04.458
Whosever running this thing
told them to blame me.

02:04.458 --> 02:07.195
- We have two priests, Captain,

02:07.195 --> 02:10.564
Father Eugene O'Hanigan
and Monsignor Patrick Mulregan,

02:10.564 --> 02:12.900
who confirm parts of the story.

02:12.900 --> 02:15.236
Are you saying they're in
on a conspiracy too?

02:15.236 --> 02:17.070
- I don't know.

02:17.070 --> 02:19.006
Father Eugene is my cousin,

02:19.006 --> 02:22.643
so...some of this
might be personal.

02:22.643 --> 02:25.346
There is a nun, though,
a Sister Nina Kelly.

02:25.346 --> 02:26.814
She suggested to me

02:26.814 --> 02:30.284
that Father Eugene
was somehow involved.

02:30.284 --> 02:32.253
Have you spoken to her yet?

02:32.253 --> 02:35.256
[tense music]

02:35.256 --> 02:43.397
*

02:53.874 --> 02:56.143
- Sister,
is anyone else coming?

02:56.143 --> 02:59.247
- Not today.
Just--just get in.

03:04.452 --> 03:05.853
- Barba.

03:05.853 --> 03:07.288
- We're not supposed
to be talking.

03:07.288 --> 03:08.622
- No?

03:08.622 --> 03:10.758
Did you know
that I was getting transferred?

03:10.758 --> 03:12.793
- 1PP doesn't keep
the DA's office apprised

03:12.793 --> 03:15.896
of its Byzantine maneuvers.
- No? Well, let me fill you in.

03:15.896 --> 03:18.266
You told them
about me and Tucker,

03:18.266 --> 03:20.634
and a few hours later
I'm getting pep talks

03:20.634 --> 03:22.303
about what a great asset
that I would be

03:22.303 --> 03:23.904
to women
in Community Affairs.

03:23.904 --> 03:25.306
- Liv, you're seeing someone
I'm investigating.

03:25.306 --> 03:26.740
1PP had to know.

03:26.740 --> 03:29.109
- Tucker is not
a sex trafficker.

03:29.109 --> 03:30.544
- Then the investigation
will clear him.

03:30.544 --> 03:32.413
Until it does,
just stay out of it.

03:32.413 --> 03:35.383
- Whoever's behind this
murdered Cara,

03:35.383 --> 03:39.487
and while you and 1PP
are chasing their Trojan horse,

03:39.487 --> 03:42.290
other girls are in danger.

03:42.290 --> 03:44.091
- We can't talk about this.

03:44.091 --> 03:45.459
- Wha--

03:46.760 --> 03:50.298
[cell phone rings]

03:50.298 --> 03:52.333
Hello?
- This is Nina.

03:52.333 --> 03:54.635
Did you tell them that
I'm not cooperating anymore?

03:54.635 --> 03:56.704
- Okay, Nina...
Nina, where are you?

03:56.704 --> 03:58.839
- Jus--just tell them
that I'm leaving town

03:58.839 --> 04:00.140
and that they don't have
to worry about me.

04:00.140 --> 04:02.310
- Wait, Nina, wait.
Listen to me--

04:02.310 --> 04:04.545
- I have to go.
- Nina, hold on--

04:04.545 --> 04:05.813
- Nina? Hello?

04:05.813 --> 04:08.816
[suspenseful music]

04:08.816 --> 04:16.857
*

04:39.413 --> 04:42.416
[dramatic music]

05:25.426 --> 05:25.559
.

05:27.795 --> 05:28.028
- Ed, hey.

05:30.297 --> 05:31.899
How are you holding up?

05:31.899 --> 05:33.901
- Group One's been grilling me
since 8:00 a.m.

05:33.901 --> 05:35.803
- They can't think
that you're in on this.

05:35.803 --> 05:38.205
- Oh, yeah, they can.
What do you got?

05:38.205 --> 05:39.973
- You need to be careful.

05:39.973 --> 05:43.411
Somebody's after Sister Nina,
and you might be next.

05:43.411 --> 05:44.645
- What are you talking about?

05:44.645 --> 05:46.847
- She called me this morning,
spooked,

05:46.847 --> 05:48.982
and now I can't reach her.

05:48.982 --> 05:50.851
Dodds is tracking her phone.

05:50.851 --> 05:54.021
- Great.
All right, keep me posted.

05:54.021 --> 05:56.023
Listen, I'm due back upstairs.

05:56.023 --> 05:59.860
More questions about
me and my cousin Eugene.

05:59.860 --> 06:01.662
*

06:01.662 --> 06:04.798
- Okay, I know
you can't violate any oaths,

06:04.798 --> 06:06.233
but when these girls
confessed to you--

06:06.233 --> 06:07.568
- I became concerned

06:07.568 --> 06:09.970
that the girls
were being preyed upon

06:09.970 --> 06:13.306
by the two vice cops,
and I suggested to the monsignor

06:13.306 --> 06:17.778
that he talk to my cousin
in Internal Affairs.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.513
- When was this?
- A year ago,

06:19.513 --> 06:21.615
March 14th--that's the date
of the letter

06:21.615 --> 06:24.017
I sent to Ed Tucker
outlining these crimes.

06:24.017 --> 06:26.019
- You still have that letter
on your computer?

06:26.019 --> 06:28.456
- I write by hand,
but I kept a photocopy

06:28.456 --> 06:30.491
if you'd like to see that.

06:30.491 --> 06:33.260
- Yeah, please.

06:33.260 --> 06:36.196
Yep, last March, hmm.

06:36.196 --> 06:38.198
And you--are you sure
he got this?

06:38.198 --> 06:40.668
I me--did you hear back
from Captain Tucker?

06:40.668 --> 06:43.203
- Tucker calls my partner
and I

06:43.203 --> 06:44.838
and says he wants to meet.

06:44.838 --> 06:47.808
- When was this?
- March 16th, last year.

06:47.808 --> 06:51.044
Here's a print out
of Detective Russo's calendar.

06:51.044 --> 06:53.280
- Was your lawyer or rep
with you?

06:53.280 --> 06:55.816
- No, Tucker said
that it was off the record,

06:55.816 --> 06:57.485
strictly for intel.

06:57.485 --> 07:00.287
So we go to--
- Wait just a minute.

07:00.287 --> 07:01.722
Let me make clear

07:01.722 --> 07:03.924
anything my client
says to implicate Tucker

07:03.924 --> 07:05.392
cannot be used against him.

07:05.392 --> 07:06.527
- Go on.

07:06.527 --> 07:07.928
- We go down.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.396
Tucker's there
without his partner,

07:09.396 --> 07:12.600
says he knows about us
and the girls

07:12.600 --> 07:15.102
and that it can go
one of two ways:

07:15.102 --> 07:18.906
We lose our badges
and we do some hard time,

07:18.906 --> 07:21.975
or we cut him in
on our action

07:21.975 --> 07:24.244
and he closes
this file out.

07:24.244 --> 07:26.279
- Do you have any way
to verify this?

07:26.279 --> 07:27.781
Were the meetings
with Tucker recorded?

07:27.781 --> 07:31.251
- No, it was Tucker,
my partner, and me.

07:31.251 --> 07:32.786
I told my captain
about it.

07:32.786 --> 07:34.955
[knocks on glass]

07:34.955 --> 07:37.758
- Yeah, give me a few minutes.

07:45.098 --> 07:46.934
That guy's got his story down.

07:46.934 --> 07:48.802
- Well, if Jefferson and Russo
met with Tucker,

07:48.802 --> 07:50.003
IAB is sure to have
a record of it.

07:50.003 --> 07:52.673
[door opens]
- Hey, Sergeant,

07:52.673 --> 07:55.075
this is a copy of the letter
the monsignor sent Tucker

07:55.075 --> 07:57.277
outing the vice cops.

07:57.277 --> 07:58.812
- Either Tucker's dirty

07:58.812 --> 08:00.548
or somebody's
setting him up good.

08:00.548 --> 08:02.215
- Okay, I'll give this
to Group One.

08:02.215 --> 08:04.017
Next problem,
the lieutenant called.

08:04.017 --> 08:05.753
Sister Nina might be in trouble,

08:05.753 --> 08:07.688
and her burner phone's
going straight to voicemail.

08:07.688 --> 08:09.156
- A burner--so no GPS.

08:09.156 --> 08:10.791
- TARU just triangulated.

08:10.791 --> 08:13.193
The last call came
from Saxon Woods.

08:13.193 --> 08:16.096
I got an emergency exception to
put a Triggerfish on her phone.

08:16.096 --> 08:18.098
If it's on, we'll find it.

08:18.098 --> 08:19.567
- Where was the last
call made from?

08:19.567 --> 08:21.902
- TARU said
less than a mile from here.

08:21.902 --> 08:23.571
- The minivan
is Nina Kelly's?

08:23.571 --> 08:25.873
- No, it belongs to
an Episcopal Church in Yonkers.

08:25.873 --> 08:27.174
I left word.

08:27.174 --> 08:30.043
- Can you call again?
- Sure.

08:30.043 --> 08:32.279
- Well, somebody
ran her off the road.

08:32.279 --> 08:35.448
- Yeah, and look.
You see these drag marks?

08:35.448 --> 08:37.450
Go over here
to the tire tracks.

08:37.450 --> 08:39.587
So they--they put her
in their vehicle

08:39.587 --> 08:41.221
and they took off.
- That's not good.

08:41.221 --> 08:43.924
- No.
- I got two suitcases.

08:47.394 --> 08:49.763
- It's women's clothes.

08:49.763 --> 08:51.832
This one is Nina's.

08:51.832 --> 08:55.402
[police radio chatter]

08:55.402 --> 08:58.639
And that one looks like
a teenage girl's, right?

08:58.639 --> 09:00.273
- So we got two vics.

09:00.273 --> 09:02.610
- Okay, church lady says
the van is usually driven

09:02.610 --> 09:05.613
by their reverend,
a Father Joseph Leahy.

09:05.613 --> 09:07.615
- Another priest?

09:07.615 --> 09:09.249
- You got to be kidding me.

09:12.185 --> 09:13.520
- Yes, that's our minivan.

09:13.520 --> 09:14.955
I loaned it to Nina
this morning.

09:14.955 --> 09:17.057
She said she was in trouble.
Is she okay?

09:17.057 --> 09:19.159
- Do you have any idea
where she was headed?

09:19.159 --> 09:21.795
- I gave her the keys to my
family's lake house in Vermont.

09:21.795 --> 09:23.697
- You did?

09:23.697 --> 09:25.833
All right, so you
two must be--must be close.

09:25.833 --> 09:27.400
Episcopalian reverend,
a Catholic nun.

09:27.400 --> 09:28.669
How'd you meet?

09:28.669 --> 09:30.470
- I used to be
a Catholic priest.

09:30.470 --> 09:33.506
That's when Nina and I, uh--

09:34.842 --> 09:37.310
- Became involved?

09:37.310 --> 09:39.146
- We were in love.

09:39.146 --> 09:41.548
I asked her to marry me,
to start a new life together.

09:41.548 --> 09:43.651
- But she turned you down?

09:43.651 --> 09:45.418
- She said she had
too much work to do.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.320
Girls were being abused.

09:47.320 --> 09:49.556
I asked her to stop,
but Nina's dogged.

09:49.556 --> 09:51.992
She never quits anything,
not even the Church.

09:51.992 --> 09:53.827
- When you gave her the keys
to the car,

09:53.827 --> 09:55.495
was she traveling alone?

09:55.495 --> 09:57.364
- She was very anxious
about the girls.

09:57.364 --> 09:59.532
I think she was trying
to get them out of town.

09:59.532 --> 10:01.434
- Okay, thank you.

10:01.434 --> 10:03.336
Margaret's at home.
Danielle is at the shelter.

10:03.336 --> 10:05.773
They said Nina called them,
but she wasn't making any sense.

10:05.773 --> 10:07.540
- Do you know which hospital
she went to?

10:07.540 --> 10:10.210
Okay, thank you.

10:10.210 --> 10:12.112
Natalia's foster mother
said Natalia left

10:12.112 --> 10:14.014
early this morning--
didn't say where she was going.

10:14.014 --> 10:17.517
- Now she's at the hospital?
- Yeah, she OD'd.

10:17.517 --> 10:20.187
- They should've just
let me die.

10:20.187 --> 10:22.055
I can't stop seeing her face.

10:22.055 --> 10:23.891
- Who, Sister Nina?

10:23.891 --> 10:26.593
- You're here
because you found her, right?

10:26.593 --> 10:29.797
- Right, but we need you
to tell us what happened.

10:29.797 --> 10:31.298
- No.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.133
He said he would do
the same thing to me.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.802
- "He"?
He who?

10:36.403 --> 10:40.040
Natalia, what we know--
that you were with Sister Nina

10:40.040 --> 10:41.541
when that van got rammed.

10:41.541 --> 10:43.243
- And you saw the driver.
- Right?

10:43.243 --> 10:45.045
What did he look like?

10:45.045 --> 10:47.280
- He was black.

10:47.280 --> 10:49.416
He was dressed like a priest.

10:49.416 --> 10:52.552
- Did he have an accent
when he talked to you?

10:52.552 --> 10:55.088
- African, I think.

10:55.088 --> 10:57.157
He forced Sister Nina and me
into his van,

10:57.157 --> 10:59.927
and he--he drove
into a dead end.

10:59.927 --> 11:03.964
- Mm-kay.
Go on.

11:03.964 --> 11:06.466
- He made us walk
into the woods,

11:06.466 --> 11:09.870
and, um, he said if I ran,

11:09.870 --> 11:12.339
he'd--he'd shoot her.

11:14.842 --> 11:17.644
Then he raped her.

11:17.644 --> 11:21.749
And when he was done,
he shot her anyway.

11:21.749 --> 11:23.550
He said I should tell
all the other girls that

11:23.550 --> 11:26.754
that's what would happen
to them if they talked.

11:26.754 --> 11:28.388
- And that's when you went
to score?

11:28.388 --> 11:30.657
- No, no, I didn't.

11:30.657 --> 11:33.393
He--he drove me
back to the Bronx,

11:33.393 --> 11:35.763
and he loaded that needle
in front of me,

11:35.763 --> 11:37.865
and he put it in my hand.

11:37.865 --> 11:41.101
He said,
"The Lord is my shepherd."

11:42.770 --> 11:45.773
Then I woke up here.

11:45.773 --> 11:46.774
[police radio chatter]

11:46.774 --> 11:48.108
- Tire tracks stop here.

11:48.108 --> 11:49.777
- Yeah, Natalia said
he pulled them both

11:49.777 --> 11:51.344
out of the car
and into the woods.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.246
- Can we get the dogs?

11:53.246 --> 11:56.249
[suspenseful music]

11:56.249 --> 12:04.357
*

12:11.364 --> 12:12.933
- Sergeant, they found her.

12:12.933 --> 12:14.334
Move.
Move!

12:14.334 --> 12:17.337
[somber music]

12:17.337 --> 12:23.343
*

12:23.343 --> 12:25.979
- All right, call it in.

12:28.816 --> 12:29.950
You know what?
Don't worry.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.551
I got it.

12:48.869 --> 12:49.002
.

12:50.470 --> 12:50.938
- I'm sorry, Lieutenant.

12:52.505 --> 12:54.707
- Sister Nina
wasn't paranoid at all.

12:54.707 --> 12:57.978
She was right.
What did the M.E. say?

12:57.978 --> 13:00.213
- She confirmed
what Natalia told us.

13:00.213 --> 13:02.515
Sister Nina was raped

13:02.515 --> 13:06.286
and shot point-blank.

13:06.286 --> 13:08.555
- And Natalia ID'd
Father Akintola?

13:08.555 --> 13:10.190
- Yeah, picked him
out of a photo array.

13:10.190 --> 13:11.724
Said he was wearing
his priest collar.

13:11.724 --> 13:13.326
- Where is he now?

13:13.326 --> 13:14.995
- Maybe in the wind,

13:14.995 --> 13:16.663
and nobody at St. Fabiola's
is returning our calls.

13:16.663 --> 13:18.298
- Of course they're not.

13:18.298 --> 13:20.633
Go and sit outside
their offices

13:20.633 --> 13:23.070
for as long as it takes.

13:23.070 --> 13:26.073
[dramatic music]

13:26.073 --> 13:30.710
*

13:30.710 --> 13:32.745
- Sister, any word?

13:32.745 --> 13:35.215
- I'm sorry.
It looks like the monsignor

13:35.215 --> 13:37.517
won't be coming in today
after all.

13:37.517 --> 13:39.652
- I-I thought you said
he was already here.

13:39.652 --> 13:41.088
I've been waiting
since 9:00.

13:41.088 --> 13:43.390
- Oh, you must have
misunderstood.

13:43.390 --> 13:46.559
He's in seclusion,
praying for Nina.

13:46.559 --> 13:48.395
- Monsignor Mulregan
finally called me back.

13:48.395 --> 13:50.697
He thinks Father Akintola's
out of the country.

13:50.697 --> 13:52.499
- Out of the country?

13:52.499 --> 13:54.434
- He believes the Father had
a family emergency in Cameroon

13:54.434 --> 13:56.336
three days ago.

13:56.336 --> 13:58.071
- What about Father Eugene?

13:58.071 --> 14:01.108
- Isn't he in school today?
- No, no, he's not.

14:01.108 --> 14:04.011
Sister, please, this is about
getting justice for Nina.

14:04.011 --> 14:05.946
- I understand,
but we've been told

14:05.946 --> 14:07.214
for the good of the church

14:07.214 --> 14:09.516
that it's best
not to answer any questions.

14:09.516 --> 14:11.919
- Well, who told you that?
- The monsignor.

14:11.919 --> 14:14.287
He reminded us that God's plan

14:14.287 --> 14:17.624
will be unveiled with time.

14:17.624 --> 14:19.159
- Does the monsignor

14:19.159 --> 14:21.794
know how to get
in touch with Father Akintola?

14:21.794 --> 14:25.632
- No, but Bishop Catalano
might know more.

14:25.632 --> 14:28.035
- I've been here all day.
No sign of the bishop.

14:28.035 --> 14:30.437
He's got to come in or out
at some point.

14:30.437 --> 14:32.973
Hold on--call you back.

14:37.044 --> 14:38.311
How you doing?

14:38.311 --> 14:40.480
I'm trying
to reach Bishop Catalano.

14:40.480 --> 14:42.682
- I'm sorry, Officer,
this is not a good time.

14:42.682 --> 14:44.284
- You're the bishop, aren't you?

14:44.284 --> 14:46.319
I'm looking for Father Akintola.

14:46.319 --> 14:48.655
- Call my secretary,
and she'll take care of you.

14:48.655 --> 14:50.457
- Can I please talk to you
for five minutes?

14:50.457 --> 14:53.860
- Please, we have a funeral mass
to attend to.

14:53.860 --> 15:01.501
*

15:01.501 --> 15:03.503
- Huh.
Horrifying.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.772
